claims:
Claims What is Claimed is 1. A method for modeling an IP core with an encrypted simulation model that includes a plurality of probes, comprising: activating probes of the plurality of probes in the encrypted simulation model based on a debug option; collecting data selected by the probes of the plurality of probes in the encrypted simulation model during a simulation of the IP core; performing smart diagnosis of the data in the encrypted simulation model based on a set of rules; and generating feedback messages based on the smart diagnosis . 2. The method of claim 1, wherein activating probes of the plurality of probes further comprises: activating the debug option; and in response to activating the debug option, selectively activating at least a subset of the plurality of probes in the encrypted simulation model. 3. The method of any one of claims 1-2, wherein performing smart diagnosis further comprises: determining whether at least a portion of the data violates a rule of the set of rules. 4. The method of claim 3, wherein performing smart diagnosis further comprises: in response to determining that the at least a portion of the data violates the rule of the set of rules, performing a root cause analysis to identify a reason that the data violates the rule. 5. The method of claim 4, wherein generating feedback messages further comprises: providing a suggested corrective action based on the reason that the data violates the rule. 6. The method of any one of claims 1-2, wherein collecting data further comprises: generating check points that monitor simulation signals when performing the simulation of the IP core. 7. The method of claim 6, wherein collecting data further comprises: generating variations of the simulation signals that anticipate potential error conditions. 8. The method of claim 7, wherein performing smart diagnosis further comprises: comparing the variations of the simulation signals with an expected signal to identify a reason that at least a portion of the data violates a rule of the set of rules. 9. A method for simulating an integrated circuit that includes first and second circuits, comprising: receiving first and second simulation models of the first and second circuits, respectively, wherein the second simulation model includes a plurality of probes and is encrypted; activating probes of the plurality of probes in the second simulation model; performing a simulation of the integrated circuit using the first and second simulation models; performing collection of data in the second simulation model based on the plurality of probes; 

 performing smart diagnosis in the second simulation model based on the data and a set of rules; and generating feedback messages based on a result of the smart diagnosis. 10. The method of claim 9, wherein the second simulation model further comprises: activating a debug option; and in response to activating the debug option, selectively activating at least a subset of the plurality of probes in the second simulation model. 11. The method of any one of claims 9-10, wherein performing collection of data in the second simulation model further comprises: receiving a signal from the first simulation model with the second simulation model; and generating variations of the signal to anticipate potential error conditions. 12. The method of claim 11, wherein performing smart diagnosis in the second simulation model further comprises: determining whether the signal violates a rule of the set of rules. 13. The method of claim 12, further comprising: in response to determining that the signal violates the rule of the set of rules, performing a root cause analysis to identify a reason that the signal violates the rule. 14. The method of claim 13, further comprising: 

 providing a suggested corrective action to prevent that the signal violates the rule based on the reason that the data violates the rule. 15. The method of any one of claims 13-14, wherein performing the root cause analysis further comprises: comparing the variations of the signal with an expected signal to identify the reason that the signal violates the rule. 16. A non-transitory computer-readable data storage medium encoded with instructions for modeling an IP core with a simulation model that is at least partially encrypted and includes probes, the instructions comprising: collecting data selected by the probes during a simulation of the IP core that compares simulated behavior with expected behavior of the IP core; performing smart diagnosis by generating variations of the data and analyzing the data and the variations of the data based on a set of rules; and generating feedback messages based on the smart diagnosis . 17. The non-transitory computer-readable data storage medium of claim 16, further comprising instructions for: activating a debug option; in response to activating the debug option, selectively activating at least a subset of the probes; and generating check points that monitor the data at the at least a subset of the probes. 18. The non-transitory computer-readable data storage medium of claim 16, wherein performing smart diagnosis further comprises instructions for: determining whether the data violates a rule of the set of rules. 19. The non-transitory computer-readable data storage medium of claim 18, further comprising instructions for: in response to determining that the data violates the rule of the set of rules, determining whether one of the variations of the data respects the rule; and in response to determining that the one of the variations of the data respects the rule, comparing the data with the one of the variations of the data to determine a root cause. 20. The non-transitory computer-readable data storage medium of claim 19, further comprising instructions for: determining a suggested corrective action based on the root cause. 21. A method for simulating an integrated circuit that includes first and second circuits, comprising: receiving first and second simulation models of the first and second circuits, respectively, wherein the second simulation model includes probes and is encrypted; collecting data selected by the probes in the second simulation model during a simulation of the integrated circuit ; performing smart diagnosis in the second simulation model based on the data and a set of rules; and generating feedback messages based on a result of the smart diagnosis. 22. The method of claim 21, further comprising: activating a debug option in the second simulation model; and in response to activating the debug option, selectively activating the probes in the second simulation model. 23. The method of any one of claims 21-22, wherein performing smart diagnosis in the second simulation model further comprises : receiving a signal from the first simulation model with the second simulation model; and generating variations of the signal to anticipate potential error conditions. 24. The method of claim 23, wherein performing smart diagnosis in the second simulation model further comprises: determining whether the signal violates a rule of the set of rules; and in response to determining that the signal violates the rule of the set of rules, performing a root cause analysis to identify a reason that the signal violates the rule. 25. The method of claim 24, further comprising: providing a suggested corrective action to prevent that the signal violates the rule based on the reason that the data violates the rule.
